    .hidden.carousel-nav-arrow.arrow-left[data-type='prev']
    .hidden.carousel-nav-arrow.arrow-right[data-type='next']
    .columns.small-12
      .row
        ul.carousel-infographic
          li.carousel-infographic-0
            span.infographic-label: span Write Plan
            span.infographic-cell Habitat Studio
          li.carousel-infographic-1
            span.infographic-label: span Build
            span.infographic-cell Habitat Builder
          li.carousel-infographic-2
            span.infographic-label: span Deploy
            span.infographic-cell.logos-deploy title="Docker, Kubernetes, CoreOS, Mesos"
          li.carousel-infographic-3
            span.infographic-label: span Run
            span.infographic-cell.logos-run title="Cloud Foundry, Mesosphere, VMware"
          li.carousel-infographic-4
            span.infographic-label: span Manage
            span.infographic-cell Habitat Supervisor
      .row.home--carousel-content
        .carousel-nav-arrow.arrow-left[data-type='prev']
        .carousel-nav-arrow.arrow-right[data-type='next']
        .columns.small-12.carousel-slide
          .row.carousel-slide-title
            .columns.small-12.h3.text-align-center Write a Habitat plan for your application
          .row.carousel-bullets
            .columns.small-12.medium-3.medium-offset-1
              p Create your application in your language and code editor of choice.
            .columns.small-12.medium-4
              p Define your application using a Habitat plan to create an immutable artifact with tunable configuration values.
            .columns.small-12.medium-3.end
              p Use Habitat Studio to test your plan and application, and build and iterate quickly.
          .row.carousel-cta
            .columns.small-12.text-align-center
              = link_to 'Get Started with Studio', '/demo/packaging-system/steps/1/', class: 'button cta'
        .columns.small-12.carousel-slide
          .row.carousel-slide-title
            .columns.small-12.h3.text-align-center Build your application
          .row.carousel-bullets
            .columns.small-12.medium-5.medium-offset-1
              p Use Habitat Builder and the On-Prem Habitat Builder depot to automate your application builds and have complete control over your build and runtime dependencies and transitive dependencies.
            .columns.small-12.medium-5.end
              p Optionally, export your package into a variety of formats with Builder: Docker Image, ACI, Tarball, CloudFoundry, and more.
          .row.carousel-cta
            .columns.small-12.text-align-center
              = link_to 'Get Started with Builder', '/demo/build-system/steps/1/', class: 'button cta'
        .columns.small-12.carousel-slide
          .row.carousel-slide-title
            .columns.small-12.h3.text-align-center Deploy your application
          .row.carousel-bullets
            .columns.small-12.medium-3.medium-offset-1
              p Deploy your application updates to your running services by defining your service groups' update strategies and subscribing to Builder channels.
            .columns.small-12.medium-4
              p Get automatic rebuilds when a new version of your application's underlying dependencies is available.
            .columns.small-12.medium-3.end
              p Export your application to a variety of container formats and publish them automatically to Docker Hub, ECR, and Kubernetes.
        .columns.small-12.carousel-slide
          .row.carousel-slide-title
            .columns.small-12.h3.text-align-center Run your application
          .row.carousel-bullets
            .columns.small-12.medium-3.medium-offset-1
              p Habitat's runtime automation runs your application's lifecycle hooks so your services behave intelligently over the course of their lifetime.
            .columns.small-12.medium-4
              p Templatize your configuration settings and update them as needed during runtime.
            .columns.small-12.medium-3.end
              p Your application will know how to behave as a member of a distributed system, wherever you choose to export and run it.
        .columns.small-12.carousel-slide
          .row.carousel-slide-title
            .columns.small-12.h3.text-align-center Manage your application
          .row.carousel-bullets
            .columns.small-12.medium-3.medium-offset-1
              p Check the status of your services via a customizable health check API endpoint.
            .columns.small-12.medium-4
              p See exactly what software versions you are running in each environment. Have complete dependency and transitive dependency control and visibility.
            .columns.small-12.medium-3.end
              p Health and event data is gathered from your services and placed on a queue you can use to feed your monitoring systems.
          .row.carousel-cta
            .columns.small-12.text-align-center
              = link_to 'Get Started with Supervisor', '/demo/process-supervisor/steps/1/', class: 'button cta'
